The paper studies the information spreading in Mobile Ad-Hoc Networks, which involves the interaction and communication between multiple agents. This falls under the category of Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA). The paper also deals with the transmission of information and the completion time of a protocol, which are topics related to Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The use of random walks and the analysis of a random process make this paper relevant to the field of Stochastic Processes (cs.SI). The paper also provides bounds on the completion time, which involves the analysis of algorithms and complexity theory, falling under the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with the transmission of information in a network, which is a topic related to Information Theory (cs.IT).
